&-{8Q^2\over kr^2}(\fa +\fb)+{8Q\over k}\delta H_{012}. \cr}
\eqn\pippo
$$
After defining $\chi_{\alpha \beta}\dot =\chi_{\alpha, \beta}-
\chi_{\beta, \alpha}$, we are now ready to write all the perturbation
equations at first order:
$$
\eqalign{&\chi_{23,3}-e^{-2f_0}\chi_{20,0}=0, \cr}
\eqn\diciannovea
$$
$$
