Following the ansatz \sedicibis~on the perturbations of the metric we
shall divide our equations \diciannovea-\diciannoves~into two sets which
we will call
``{\it axial}'' and ``{\it polar}''. The equations for the axial (polar)
perturbations will contain
only $\delta H_{1\alpha \beta}, \chi_0, \chi_2, \chi_3$ ($\delta H_{320}, \fa ,
\fb , \fc , \fd , \fx$).
The behaviour of the perturbations which is consistent with the simmetries of
our previous ansatz is:
$$
\cases{

